Emergency services are currently on high alert after a drive-by shooting on Meridian Drive in uMhlanga Ridge left one person dead. In a statement by Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA), officers were dispatched after residents reported rapid gunfire in the vicinity. “The driver of a white Toyota Corolla Cross had been shot while seated in his vehicle and was declared deceased on scene. Upon further inspection, it was observed that the deceased’s vehicle was shot multiple times and several rifle cartridges were found on scene,” RUSA spokesperson, Prem Balram, said. The motive for the shooting has not been established at this stage.